ntwillen man Zwang gegen den Willen eines Mitglieds einer zivilisierten Gemeinschaft rechtmäßig ausüben darf, der ist: die Schädigung anderer zu verhüten“. In diesem Band wird in Form eines kooperativen Kommentars Mills Hauptwerk Über die Freiheit für Studierende, Lehrende und Forscher aufgeschlossen und interpretiert.  aThis work provides an interpretation of John Stuart Mill’s On Liberty (1859) and elucidates the fundamental principles of Mill’s concept of liberty. For Mill, the right to form one’s own convictions and live according to them should only be infringed upon for one reason, namely “to prevent harm to others”.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLiberty. 4aGesellschaft. 4aLiberalismus. 4aSelbstbestimmung. 4aZwang. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aLiberalism, society, enforcement, self-determination.1 aBuchmüller-Codoni, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHöffe, Otfried, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHöntzsch, Frauke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNiesen, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiley, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchefczyk, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchefczyk, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchmidt-Petri, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchramme, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchramme, Thomas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStepanians, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolf, Jean-Cl